# Strobe Engine — the glint: ring modulation with oscillator two an
# OCTAVE AND A FIFTH up (~3f). The ring products land at 2f and 4f —
# pure octaves of the struck note — so the bell is glassy but never
# leaves the key. (A fifth up gives 2.5f, a major-third partial that
# sours minor keys; a tritone belongs to no key at all.)
